[{"short_id":"vzqap2","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vzqap2","created_at":"2024-11-21T19:57:04.000-06:00","title":"Arcan: A deeper dive into the SHMIF IPC system","url":"https://arcan-fe.com/2024/11/21/a-deeper-dive-into-the-shmif-ipc-system/","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vzqap2/arcan_deeper_dive_into_shmif_ipc_system","submitter_user":"dubiouslittlecreature","user_is_author":false,"tags":["compsci","graphics"]},{"short_id":"vajg5m","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vajg5m","created_at":"2024-11-21T18:16:57.000-06:00","title":"What is the \"boring technology\" solution for running multiple containers on a single host in production in 2024?","url":"","score":16,"flags":0,"comment_count":20,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI feel like this is such a common pattern at this point that there should be a \u003cem\u003emuch\u003c/em\u003e clearer go-to solution than there is. OCI containers are the lingua franca of software distribution now – why does it seem like the only option for deploying them that claims to be “production ready” is Kubernetes?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m currently responsible for one environment that uses Docker Compose to do this, but it has some sharp edges and I’ve read enough horror stories to believe it’s not a clear winner. Also unless I’m mistaken, I’m pretty sure that Docker itself recommends against this. Also there’s the infamous (and deeply frustrating) iptables problem.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m very aware of Podman, and though I’ve read much of the documentation and toyed with it a bit, I’ve not used it in production. When I investigated a year ago it seemed like everything was about deploying things with Kubernetes manifests. Now it seems like most new reference guides are about using Podman with Kubernetes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePeople who are architecting your production environment with containers on a VM: how are you doing it and is it exceedingly boring? Please share the love if so.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I feel like this is such a common pattern at this point that there should be a *much* clearer go-to solution than there is. OCI containers are the lingua franca of software distribution now -- why does it seem like the only option for deploying them that claims to be \"production ready\" is Kubernetes?\r\n\r\nI'm currently responsible for one environment that uses Docker Compose to do this, but it has some sharp edges and I've read enough horror stories to believe it's not a clear winner. Also unless I'm mistaken, I'm pretty sure that Docker itself recommends against this. Also there's the infamous (and deeply frustrating) iptables problem.\r\n\r\nI'm very aware of Podman, and though I've read much of the documentation and toyed with it a bit, I've not used it in production. When I investigated a year ago it seemed like everything was about deploying things with Kubernetes manifests. Now it seems like most new reference guides are about using Podman with Kubernetes.\r\n\r\nPeople who are architecting your production environment with containers on a VM: how are you doing it and is it exceedingly boring? Please share the love if so.","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vajg5m/what_is_boring_technology_solution_for","submitter_user":"stillgreenmoss","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","devops"]},{"short_id":"e2xlkr","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/e2xlkr","created_at":"2024-11-21T17:13:43.000-06:00","title":"Memory management and safety in Bismuth VM","url":"https://enikofox.com/posts/memory-management-and-safety-in-bismuth-vm/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/e2xlkr/memory_management_safety_bismuth_vm","submitter_user":"jado","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming"]},{"short_id":"e8tg67","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/e8tg67","created_at":"2024-11-21T17:10:25.000-06:00","title":"OSC5